Job Description:
Graduate Data Analyst
Jumbo Interactive (ASX: JIN) is a leading digital retailer of official government and charitable lotteries. We utilise the latest technology to craft an engaging and entertaining purchase experience for our customers across a range of digital platforms.
Why work at Jumbo
Our offices are open, highly collaborative and yes, fun! To support you at work (and play) we offer some fantastic benefits: flexible working hours including work from home options, the latest technology, extended parental leave, wellness program, paid team lunches/events and most importantly we have our chef providing you delicious and healthy lunches every day and breakfast twice a week when your in the office.
Your Career At Jumbo
Our 12-month program will see you placed within our data team where you will quickly gain on-the-job experience and training as well as be making meaningful contributions to your team and Jumbo's business units.
Graduates who successfully complete the program will be considered for an ongoing position, based on performance, skills and career goals. This is a full time position, with a flexible start date either late 2020 or early 2021.
Who we're looking for:
At Jumbo the role of a Graduate Data Analyst means you'll be responsible for analysing information, conducting research and implementing analytical solutions for both Marketing and Product departments.
As part of your role, we'll expect you to:
Participate in the end-to-end quantitative research projects including the design and delivery of research programs to inform strategic and operational improvements in marketing and product.
Transform analytical output into actionable insights, and proactively engage with key stakeholders by supplying customer insights and assisting with recommendations.
Support the design and development of performance dashboards and reports to inform planning and performance optimisation.
Analyse and interpret trends and patterns in customer activity, communicate results and offer potential solutions.
Complete ad-hoc analysis requests from the business departments
As a recent graduate we'd like you to bring to this role:
Degree (or equivalent) in Business/Marketing/Computer Science or related field.
An eagerness to providing recommendations that will impact the businesses growth and profit agendas directly
Strong quantitative research and analytical skills
Ability to work independently
Ability to influence others to gain buy-in and alignment
Moderate to high competency with Excel/ Google Sheets
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organise, analyse and communicate complex and varied information
Strong written and verbal ability to communicate ideas through data

About the opportunity
Being part of NSW Health Pathology means you’re helping create better health and justice systems every day.
We operate more than 60 laboratories and around 200 collection centres across NSW and conduct over 60 million tests per annum. Our network of pathologists are supported by scientists, technicians and support staff who quickly and accurately assess samples so clinical teams can make the best possible treatment decisions for patients. Our Forensic & Analytical Science Service provides independent, objective analysis to the NSW criminal and coronial justice systems.

Accrued Days Off in addition to Annual Leave
Generous salary packaging options and other fringe benefits
Corporate wellbeing programs, including the Fitness Passport
Learning and development opportunities, including in-house training with RTO My Health Learning

To assist in the development and maintenance of NSW Health Pathology’s Statewide Business Intelligence (BI) platform and the timely delivery of insights to its corporate portfolios and operational areas.

Tertiary qualifications from a relevant discipline such as IT, Mathematics, Engineering, Statistics, Science, or professional experience in business intelligence.
Experience in manipulating and transforming data through use of one or more of the following tools / languages: Excel, PowerPivot, SQL, Python, R, SSIS or Data Factory.
Experience in modelling and aggregating datasets through use of one or more of the following tools / languages: Excel / Pivot tables, PowerPivot, DAX, M, Power BI, SQL, Python, R, SSAS / tabular models.
Demonstrated awareness of cloud data and analytics solutions such as Microsoft Azure.
Experience in, or exposure to, data visualisation techniques, including the use of Microsoft Power BI or similar software.
Excellent written and oral communication skills and problem solving skills.
Ability to effectively document processes, procedures and/or code in a collaborative environment including source control, writing briefs and technical manuals for management and staff.

Opportunity to join a team of passionate & supportive industry leading experts where you can really drive your future career
The purpose of Technical & Sustainability (T&S) in Anglo American is to drive the future of mining. To do this, we need wide-ranging information and organizational knowledge, both to support decision-making across our business, and to provide the raw material for accountability. Data Analytics teams process, analyse, share and visualize this information, aiding in the process of knowledge aggregation and transformation.
We are continually seeking new ways to bring our data together to inform big-picture decision-making, from pit to port, from sensor to desktop. Harnessing the power of data analytics enables us to link planning and operations and to unlock value across the full breadth of our operations.
Anglo American aspires to become the most valued mining company in the world. We're looking for talented people who share our values and our belief in a better future for mining. If you have the relevant skills and experience in Data Analytics, we'd like to hear from you.
Job Description
Programme Data Analyst
Reporting to the Principal Programme Manager – Data Analytics, you will be a key member of the Group Data Analytics Delivery team, and partner with relevant Business Unit SME’s to understand the questions they are trying to address to unlock value, and the data they have or need to collect to address the question and extract value. This role will be based in our Brisbane Corporate Office.
This role will be rewarding and varied and will see you:
Effectively and autonomously manage your own scope, priorities and deadlines across a number of data projects, with regular routine communication, and coordination with the Principal Programme Manager, project managers and business analysts.
Be the central point of contact for data discovery and data analysis for the relevant business unit data projects and provide expertise for other areas as required.
Refine opportunities and develop a pathway for value generating data projects and provide thought leadership on opportunities and technical direction
Perform exploratory data analysis and provide rapid iterations of analysis to refine posed problems, and identify potential solutions.
Assist and support Data Engineers in developing and deploying production workflows for taking data in real-time or periodically from sites / business functions, passing the data through the developed models and producing the relevant reporting without human intervention.
Work with and support the IM department and the business unit’s analytics centre on accessing relevant analytics tools and developed models.
Work with and support the IM department and the business unit’s analytics centre in the architecture of data analytics solutions as required.
Support regional Data Analytics Product Management with technical requirements analyses, advice and product backlog maintenance through stakeholder engagement and planning.

Qualifications
To be successful in this role, you will have the following:
Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, or Engineering.
Extensive experience in data analytics, preferably in the mining industry.
Experience in designing and managing complex data projects using the relevant Azure services or similar.
Demonstrated success working with multidisciplinary technical and global teams.
Extensive experience in Exploratory data analysis with the purpose of informing user requirements and solution design / architecture.
Extensive Experience in using SQL (and Python) and connecting to various structured and semi-structured data sources.
Experience with Agile Project Management Principles and using MS DevOps.
Working knowledge of common machine learning algorithms used in regression and classification is highly desirable.
Additional Information
What we offer
When you join Anglo American, you can expect to enjoy a competitive salary and benefits package. But more than this, you’ll find yourself in an environment where the opportunities for learning and growth are second to none. From technical training to leadership programmes, we bring out the best in our people. There are plenty of opportunities to move onwards and upwards too. We’re a large, successful multinational company – and we’re still growing all the time.
Who we are?
We aim to lead the industry by pursuing ever safer and more responsible ways of working, demonstrating integrity and showing care and respect for people and the planet. That means we are constantly seeking new opportunities to mine and process our products sustainably, using less water, less energy and more precise extraction technologies. As the custodians of coal and other precious natural resources – diamonds (through De Beers), copper, platinum and other precious metals, iron ore and nickel – our extraordinary teams work safely and collaboratively, with the utmost consideration for local communities, our customers and the world at large.
Inclusion and Diversity
We strive to create an inclusive environment for all employees. Women, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders are encouraged to apply for all vacant positions.
As well as a very competitive salary package, Anglo American offers exceptional training and development opportunities to all employees.
Apply today if you want to work with the latest technology and innovation, in an environment where we challenge you to drive positive change.

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest


Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1
Salary range: $74,406.00 - $100,090.00
Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

Key skills required
1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.
Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Weekend work required


Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

Our Commitment to Diversity
NSW Health values diversity and is committed to building an inclusive workplace culture that reflects the community we serve. We encourage applications from diverse community groups including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, LGBTIQ+, those with special needs and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

For any technical issues, contact Recruitment at HSSG-Recruitment@health.nsw.gov.au.

Please note that not everyone who expresses their interest will be called to work in the centres.

Job Description: Data Analyst

About Swanky

We are a fast-growing Digital Consulting and eCommerce agency. We are leaders in the Shopify movement in Europe and are quickly making inroads into the US, Canadian and Australian markets.

Our focus is on creating nimble, flexible and cost-effective enterprise ecommerce solutions using Shopify Plus - the fastest growing Enterprise eCommerce platform on the planet.

Our growth has been achieved by helping our clients maximise their commercial potential through our Growth Accelerator service. Within the Growth Accelerator team, we have specialists that make up a full-service ecommerce function: CRO strategists, Performance Marketeers, UX Designers, SEO & Content Specialists & Project Managers.

We are looking for a Data Analyst with experience in CRO and customer insight development to help us cement our position as the best agency in the sector

Responsibility / Skills

Develop our analytical process - particularly expediting how we turn customer data into insight and therefore action
Developing flexible insight solutions across every stage of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion and retention) to facilitate quicker learnings.
Coaching and mentoring to up skill the company through advancing their use of data, including analysis, interpretation and presentation of data
Turn data and ideas into action by supporting the team with test ideation, strategy and presentation (including supporting with every stage of the testing process)
Internal reporting - this role could handle internal reporting (on our impact), and client reporting (both internally for learning and for the client) with a view to establishing ourselves as the source of truth for our clients data-led decisions
Research and development - advising and assisting with the analytical setup and ongoing management of new websites. To include the research and development of analytical opportunities during and prior to the new build stage of client engagement

This will involve having skills in the following areas:

Data analysis across all stages of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion & retention) and all areas of ecommerce performance.
Being able to create a story that communicates customer behaviour and reporting on client performance.
Being data curious and have the capability to out what the data says, and more importantly, why
Be a great data communicator - being able to relay data in a way that is accessible to everyone
Enjoy collaborating on projects
Be able to create an insight generation programme, including knowing how to understand the customer, process and interpret the data
Be a problem solver and enjoy being able to find the solution to a business/customer issue

Requirements

(Ideally) proven experience in a data analytics and conversion rate optimisation role
(Ideally) experience using split testing software
Familiarity with Agile frameworks
Ability to document and troubleshoot errors
Excellent communication skills
Attention to detail
Analytical mind and problem-solving aptitude
Strong organisational skills
Familiarity with web technologies such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript useful but not a pre-requisite

Benefits:

Starting salary of $60k-$75k
Opportunity to grow and shape the position
Personal development within a fast-growing company
Opportunities to travel to work with remote working teams
Collaborative, creative working environment
Regular company socials and events, including Games Nights, and lunchtime sports

How will I help?

Fantastic Opportunity for a Data and Reporting Analyst, you will be a key member of Customer Assist within Group Operations and your role is paramount to helping deliver Westpac’s vision and strategic priorities.

You will be responsible in delivering commercial insights and reporting/analytics solutions to support informed management decision making with regards to customer and commercial outcomes and engaging with the BI and analytics teams transforming analytical output into actionable commercial insights, build partner materials and engage with stakeholders throughout the process.

We have multiple opportunities across Adelaide and Sydney.

What’s in it for me?

You’ll play an important and significant part in the future of a business that has been around for 200 years. Our vision is to become one of the world’s great service companies.

So, we’ll back you in the development of your career, with internal career prospects and flexible working.

You’ll also be backed by a fantastic team of people in a can-do, supportive structure.

What do I need?

This role frequently works with subject matter experts across the business for developing, creating and implementation of all project deliverables, and in conjunction with other analyst, change and project managers for coordination and delivery of content across multiple portfolios.

You will demonstrate:
Confidence in providing strategic insights to the business to drive portfolio optimisation
Strong communication and stakeholder management
Should be confident to analyse and present complex business problems and its analytical solutions to non-technical audience
Technical expertise in Excel and PowerPoint.
Background in Digital Design / Visualisation is highly desirable.

What is it like to work there?

As well as good pay and a great culture, joining the Westpac family means you’ll get some of the best banking, wealth and insurance benefits in the market.

We back our employees by helping them work towards industry-recognised qualifications, using online learning, training modules and career planning tools for you to grow with us. We’ll even pay you to do volunteer or community work.

As an equal opportunity employer, we’re proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility – and champions inclusion.

How do I Apply?

Start here. Just click on the APPLY button.

As part of our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, this role is open to experienced candidates seeking a discussion around workplace flexibility. We invite candidates of all ages, people with a disability and Indigenous Australians to apply.

The health and wellbeing of our employees is our top priority. We’ve developed clear standards to ensure our people are confident, safe and healthy whether they’re working from a Westpac Group site or working from home. These are based on expert medical advice and Safe Work Australia guidelines.

An opportunity to grow your career and learn in a supportive environment.
To work with like-minded people that are passionate about data analytics and business intelligence.

To work with a team that supports, challenges and invests in their top talent.

Ability to write complex SQL (stored procedures, triggers and views).
Experience with Business Intelligence software, specifically the Power Platform and the Tableau Product family.
Experience in predictive analytics techniques and data modelling.
The energy and attitude to join a young and ambitious team that prides itself on being innovative intrapreneurs.
High level of written and verbal communication skills.

Job Title: Data Analyst @ Big Picture - Full Flexibility / WFH
Entry Level Intelligence Analyst (Full Training Provided)
Job Description:
Your role:
A role as an Entry Level Intelligence Analyst (known in the Navy as Cryptologic Linguist) is exciting, challenging and immensely rewarding. You’ll use language and analytical skills to provide key information to the Command team. You’ll be supported by classified Government intelligence programs to analyse, interpret and translate foreign language material in real-time; both at sea and ashore. The intelligence that you provide has a direct impact on operations all around the world.
Whilst all Intelligence Analysts receive formal language training they do not normally perform the role of an interpreter or other linguistics roles not associated with their primary intelligence role.
Teamwork is an important part of the role. You’ll work in a close-knit team that really rely on each other. There are also many opportunities for career growth and travel; all while making a difference to the defence of Australia and her interests.
The training Intelligence Analysts receive include, but are not limited to:
- Learning a language other than English,
- Information technology processes, like typing and software manipulation,
- Analytical techniques and methodical problem-solving,
- Communications theory and networks,
- Methods for working with intelligence information,
- The ‘order of battle’ of foreign military forces,
- Procedures for safeguarding intelligence information.
Prior experience isn’t needed. You’ll gain all the necessary skills and qualifications to become an Entry Level Intelligence Analyst as part of your training.
Life in the Navy:
A career in the Navy is a challenging and highly rewarding working environment that comes with good work/life balance, competitive salary and skills for life. You can expect to feel a unique sense of accomplishment and pride from serving and protecting our country and helping to keep our vast coastlines safe.
Life in the Navy is anything but mundane. You’ll enjoy varied lifestyles, rewarding careers, opportunities to travel, and excellent social and fitness facilities, free medical and dental; all in a dynamic and fulfilling working environment.
Don’t worry, it’s not all life at sea—there’s more to the Navy than ships, submarines and helicopters.
Some days, you might be exploring exciting new countries with your fellow crewmates. Other days, you could be stationed locally not too far from home.
Salary:
Be paid to train and learn the skills required to become a qualified Cryptologic Linguist. Upon completion of your initial military and initial employment training, you’ll enjoy a competitive starting salary package of up to: $85,154 including service and uniform allowances, as well as a Maritime Allowance (if applicable).
In addition to your salary, you will receive generous superannuation, housing subsidies and free medical and dental.
Apply Now:
For this role, you must be over 17 at time of enlistment, an Australian Citizen and have passed Year 10 English and Maths. An aptitude to learn a foreign language is essential (you’ll be tested before being accepted).

Who Are We?
At MCRI we share a powerful vision; to re-imagine the future of child health. We are the home to many life-changing scientific discoveries. We believe that no question is too impossible to try and answer. We are renowned for our cutting edge focus on early interventions, improved diagnosis, prevention and development of potential cures. Our success is founded on a philosophy of collaboration through a multi-disciplinary approach to solving the toughest questions in child health.
MCRI is a proud member of the Australian Network on Disability. We are committed to creating a positive working environment which values all backgrounds and experiences. We strive to foster an inclusive culture that is underpinned by equal opportunity for all and a culture based on respect, consideration and dignity. Don’t take our word for it, check what our employees are saying!


The Opportunity
We are looking for a data analyst to join the Health Services team at MCRI.
As our data analyst you will work on the Covid-19 pandemic restrictions: Changing patterns in health services use and indirect impacts on Victorians’ healthcare project.
The project is funded by the Melbourne Academic Centre for Health (MACH) and the Victorian Department of Health and Human Services. The project is using routinely collected Victorian administrative patient data to examine the changing patterns in health service use and indirect impacts of restrictions on health and healthcare use, because of the Covid-19 pandemic and associated restrictions.
A key part of your role will see you contribute to the project by providing support in statistical analysis, including: i) writing the statistical analysis plan in consultation with investigators;
ii) data management and cleaning; iii) conducting the analysis of linked Victorian hospital, Emergency Department and non-admitted services data from 2018-2019 and compare with data from 2020.
You will be liaising with a variety of stakeholders such as other investigators from different organisations, The Royal Children’s Hospital Health Services Research Unit, the project lead, and the extended MCRI Team. Therefore it essential you have excellent communication and engagement skills while being able to foster existing relationships.
To be successful in this role you have previous experience working in a similar role ideally in the research space on a large scale health project.
You are ready to bring value to this role through your passion and technical skills but also understand the value you will bring to Children’s future health.
Your responsibilities will include but are not limited to:
Developing the statistical analysis plan in collaboration with lead investigators
Data cleaning, management and analysis of linked administrative health data
Contributing to following and maintaining good data management practices including data storage and backup procedures.
Creating/overseeing final annotated program files (Stata do‐files) that become the permanent, concise record of a coherent set of analyses.
Contributing to the write‐up of reports and peer‐reviewed publications arising from the research, with co-authorship where intellectual contribution warrants.
Conducts ethical research at the highest level of integrity and in line with the Australian Code for Responsible Conduct of Research and MCRI policies
You Demonstrate:
Essential:
Degree/Honours/Masters qualification in Biostatistics or related discipline
Appropriate level of statistics expertise gained from experience, training and/or professional accreditation
Demonstrated data management skills, including use of data management principles in research and practices good data management such as quality and version control
Demonstrated statistical analysis skills, including the ability to analyse large datasets reliably
Demonstrated experience using Stata statistical software (or equivalent statistical package with clear capacity to develop capability in Stata)
Demonstrated capacity to work independently and collaboratively in a team environment
Demonstrated effective administrative and organisational skills and processes, including personal time management (such as meeting project timelines and balancing competing demands)
Desirable
Experience in analysis of linked administrative health datasets such as the Victorian Admitted Episodes Dataset or Victorian Emergency Minimum Dataset
Experience conducting Interrupted Time Series analysis
Experience in peer-reviewed publications (i.e., producing results for publication, authorship)

Part time 0.6 max term contract

Job Title: Data Analyst – Product Forensics
Location: Melbourne
Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head

Join a progressive organisation with the people and policies you want
At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive and to achieve this, we need a talented Data Analyst to join our Product Forensic squad. The purpose of the Product Forensics Analytics Squad is to ensure we do the right thing by our customers, to build and sustain trust. We work to fulfil our mission through the ongoing prevention and detection of “the unexpected” so that the customer experience is seamless and reliable.
As a Senior Product Forensics Consultant focused on the newly formed Product Forensics operation/domain, you will bring extensive analytical and technical skills, business acumen and natural curiosity to support and enable your squad to deliver on a wide range of analytical investigations and initiatives to provide valued insights and enable data-driven decision making.
Additionally, you will be tried and tested methods that can be shared across the team, lead forensics engagements and investigations and mentor up and coming data analysts.

What a typical day might look like
Support individual missions of Squads through data analysis
Attend stand-up to align progress on your individual tasks
Perform product and forensics analytics to detect and prevent “the unexpected” across the Retail and Commercial Bank product sets to drive continuous improvement and positively influence strategic change
Perform deep drives into high-risk areas to determine root causes and improvement opportunities with Technology and Product areas.
Build continuous monitoring mechanisms to proactively manage, prevent and detect product risks across Australia Division and drive immediate action
Upskill product areas in data analytics to enable them to become self-sufficient

What will likely be in your toolkit?
Experiences in driving in-depth investigations or analytical engagements to uncover root causes, behaviours, trends and anomalies for decision making purposes.
Experiences in designing/building continuous monitoring and diagnostics mechanisms to scale.
Skills to quickly understand, interrogate and investigate large datasets utilising a variety of methods (SQL, Python, R) and technologies (Teradata, Hadoop, SAS, Cloudera, Excel)
Ability to break down problems and plan out manageable work activities through Human Centred Design, Hypothesis Based Thinking or Structured Problem Solving approaches.
Ability to mentor, review and challenge team members’ investigations to assure quality and outcome delivery.
Ability to communicate and present ideas and outcomes to technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Ability to manage multiple investigations at once and adapt to changing priorities and ambiguity.
You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture and we actively encourage people to try new things. So if this role interests you and you feel you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

We’re reinventing the way we do banking, and our community of collaborative, innovative thinkers who create human centred solutions are helping us get there. We’re responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter and helping people achieve incredible things – be it buying their home, building a business or saving for things big or small.

This role will enable the Research Analyst to become familiar both with a range of commodity markets, and the way Consulting execute and manage projects.

Document frameworks in clear English and Maths, following CRU templates

Customer Interaction, Market Awareness and Marketing

Contribute to commercial proposals, marketing insights and presentations

Understand customer requirements and work with colleagues to meet those needs

Take part in and contribute to customer/site visits and conference meetings as required, working with other team members and CRU Sales and Marketing team

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest

Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Senior Data Analyst be doing?
The Data Analysis Team is responsible for a wide range of data management, data cleaning and preparation and reporting activities to support NSW’s public health response to the COVID-19 pandemic.
The COVID-19 Senior Data Analyst is located within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic. The Senior Data Analyst will support the Team Leader in managing the Data Analysis Team, including providing mentorship for junior team members. The Senior Data Analyst will make a significant contribution to provision of high quality, reliable data for NSW Health and intergovernmental agencies through: managing the acquisition of COVID related data from a range of sources; guiding analysis and enhancement of data to provide reports and data visualisations; and considering strategic challenges in data acquisition and reporting in a high scrutiny environment.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 3
Salary range: $113,735.00 - $129,658.00
Hourly rate: $57.36 - $65.39

Key skills required
1. Post-graduate qualifications in epidemiology or biostatistics or equivalent in public health or related discipline and relevant experience.
2. Substantial experience in data management, analysis and reporting of health data.
3. Substantial experience with statistical packages such as SAS, Python or R.
4. Demonstrated experience in managing a team with ability to delegate effectively to achieve positive outcomes; demonstrated leadership skills with experience in developing the capability of a team, establishing, monitoring and ensuring achievement of clear performance objectives; coaching and advising staff, and fostering a collegial, professional work environment.
5. Highly developed communication, negotiation and interpersonal skills.
6. High level oral and written communication skills with demonstrated ability to prepare, review and edit correspondence, briefings, reports, research papers and project proposals, and able to interact effectively with staff, management and external stakeholders


Key accountabilities of the role
Manage the acquisition of COVID related data including preparation of data extracts.
Liaison with data providers, data users, subject matter experts and other stakeholders to ensure optimal use and translation of data.
Undertake and guide analysis and enhancement of data.
Prepare high quality data visualisations and other data products when requested.
Provide timely advice and response to data-related enquires from the PHRB teams.
Consider and develop a response to strategic challenges in data acquisition and reporting in a high scrutiny environment.
Assist the Team Leaders with team leadership and management responsibilities.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Evening and weekend work required
Apply appropriate analyses to complex data
Work across sometimes conflicting and/or contrasting requirements from different stakeholder groups
Match technical feasibility of data analyses with operational requirements

Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

NSW Health values diversity and is committed to building an inclusive workplace culture that reflects the community we serve. MCA provides the objective evidence to ensure Navy can improve current and projected maritime warfighting ability using innovative analysis techniques. These techniques include experimentation and wargaming, modelling and simulation, mathematical operations research, big data analytics and statistical analysis.

Developing, using and explaining results from computer models.

The Role
Come join a team which works collaboratively with scientists from diverse disciplines to understand, shape and improve Navy capability through innovative analysis. Your role will include the opportunity to travel interstate, observe exercises and gather data at sea on board Navy ships and work alongside Navy people.

In this role you will lead and conduct studies that consider both current warfighting operations, tactics and systems, as well as potential future systems. You will make a contribution to resolving emerging questions on how Australia’s warships should be made ready to go to sea, deploy to where they are needed, and fight to win.

Training and development opportunities will be frequently available to hone your analysis skills as they apply to this role. This position will give you the opportunity to conduct collaborative research and exploit state of the art DST private cloud and High Performance Computing infrastructure.

About our Team
Maritime Capability Analysis (MCA) Major Science and Technology Capability (MSTC) is within the Joint and Operations Analysis Division of Defence Science and Technology Group (DSTG). The diverse and inclusive team at MCA is looking to improve and expand its analysis capacity and capabilities.

MCA provides the objective evidence to ensure Navy can improve current and projected maritime warfighting ability using innovative analysis techniques. These techniques include experimentation and wargaming, modelling and simulation, mathematical operations research, big data analytics and statistical analysis.

This position is in the Maritime Simulation Experimentation and Wargaming Group based in Sydney. The work is focused on assisting Navy to make informed decisions when acquiring new platforms and systems, and providing advice on improving the warfighting impact of the Navy fleet.

Our Ideal Candidate
We are looking for an enthusiastic individual to conduct studies and analysis on naval capability and operational effectiveness. Applicants should have broad, demonstrable knowledge or experience across one or more relevant areas including:
Problem structuring;
Mathematical and statistical modelling and analysis;
Operations analysis;
Data analysis; and
Developing, using and explaining results from computer models.

Post graduate qualifications, or equivalent experience in, Operations Research, Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science or similar disciplines would be highly desirable. This role is open to a range of experience levels from recent graduate to experienced practitioner.

Candidates would be required to show initiative and innovation and be able to apply existing analytical techniques as well as researching novel approaches and applications. Applicants must have excellent verbal and written communication skills to enable you to collaborate with Navy personnel, academia and industry with clarity and influence.

Northern Health Electronic Medical Record (EMR) Project
Northern Health plans to implement an integrated Electronic Medical Record with the Vision ‘One patient’ ‘One integrated record’ and the purpose to optimise the quality and safety of our patient care. Northern Health is planning a full stack implementation to be in place by mid-2022 which will bring us to a level 5+ HIMSS EMRAM scale of EMR adoption. A large team will be hired and mobilised to plan and deliver a large scope of technical and clinical work to support the implementation and to ensure the achievement of timelines, once confirmed.
The program of work will transform how clinical care is provided to the patients and communities we serve and will be a clinically lead transformation project.

The EMR Medication Analyst will be responsible for the analysis, design, build, configuration, testing and conversion of the EMR at Northern Health. You will be responsible for the review of existing workflows, content and configuration to contribute to the optimization of current workflows and the design of new workflows.

You will have the ability to work autonomously and analyse clinical workflows, collect and review data in the data collection workbooks. The analyst will be responsible for reviewing all aspects of medication management including but not limited to drug order catalogue and formulary, additions to Pharmaceutical benefits and updates to the Cerner drug database.
Work collaboratively with the EMR team, Pharmacy Services Department and clinical staff for all EMR matters related to medication management and electronic prescribing.

A tertiary degree in healthcare, or science related field

Demonstrated experience working in a tertiary hospital environment and understanding of clinical workflows in the acute and subacute inpatient settings
Knowledge of and experience with the Cerner EMR or equivalent EMR/Clinical systems implementations
Critical thinking, strong analytical and troubleshooting skills to investigate and understand issues along with their clinical implications.

In addition, you will contribute to the continuous development of the VIPA suite of tools, making and maintaining relationships with Defence stakeholders and supporting the Senior Trainer with development and delivery of training materials.
A "Day in the Life" will see you:
Acquiring data from primary or secondary data sources and maintaining data structures
Interpreting data and analysing results using standardised techniques
Developing and implementing data analyses, data collection systems and other strategies that optimise quality
Identifying new data sources, collecting data, sourcing missing data
Generating information and insights from data sets and identifying trends and patterns including removing and cleaning data holdings
Preparing SOPS and reports for executive and project teams
Creating visualisations of VIPA data utilisation

Qualifications
About You and What You’ll Bring
We are seeking a Data Analyst who loves everything data! This includes managing data in all its forms, analysing information structures and someone who is passionate about developing innovative ways of managing the information assets of the VIPA tool.
Do you have a high attention to detail? Are you able to easily communicate with your colleagues across multiple areas (Leidos team, Defence Subject Matters Experts, other technical resources)? Can you work alone or as a part of a team? Do you have excellent verbal and written communication skills? Do you have an understanding of Defence logistics management and processes? If you had said ‘Yes’ to any of the above, keep reading!
Other skills, knowledge and experience include:
Understand the complexities involved in handling and managing Defence logistical data
Ability to apply standards, principles, theories, concepts and techniques in a technical ICT domain
Ability to identify and assess risks associated with changes in business processes, business rules and requirements
Understanding of VIPA would be advantageous (optional)
Former member of the Australian Defence Force with experience in Defence logistics
Experience with Joint military planning and operations is desirable
Certificate IV in Training and Assessment is desirable

Additional Information
What you’ll love
At Leidos you’ll enjoy 12 weeks’ paid parental leave as a primary carer, flexible work practices, discounted health insurance, novated leasing and more. Foster your career through complete access to learning and development and mentoring opportunities, we have a strong track record of internal promotion and career transitions.
Please note that this role requires routine travel within Australia.
Candidates must hold or be able to obtain a NV-1 security clearance.

At Canva, we’re transforming the way the world designs, and we need you to help us transform the way we use data to achieve that goal. The mountains of data are large, but our data team is small, and we’re looking to change that.

Our product has grown by over 25 times in the last 2 years, and we now have 10s of millions of users generating enormous quantities of data every day. To help us fuel our future growth and help even more users, we need to better understand our data - this is where we need your help.

Our Analytics folks manage huge volumes of data in order to help our friends in other teams to build the right product. You’ll be coming into a diverse team of people who really do enjoy finding answers to the problems that the business and our users have. We can often be found chatting about all the latest trends in data and how we can apply them at Canva. We’re looking forward to growing the team and gaining a range of new perspectives and ideas on how we can do things better.

Role Responsibilities
Help us understand both Canva and our customers – we want you to be creative and insightful, rather than just throwing the usual metrics at the wall to see what sticks
Suggest, set up, and run interesting experiments that will actually move our metrics – when we push tests to 100% we want to actually see the bump in the relevant graph
Build and maintain dashboards for our product teams, and make them look really good – you don’t need to be a designer or have any design talent, you just need to want to build things that look cool
Use our giant databases to answer the sort of questions that sound really simple but turn out to be challenging (and fun!)
Help us extend data literacy and curiosity throughout the whole company
Required Skills & Experience
Experience with very large data sets — if you’re familiar with that sinking feeling that your computer doesn’t have quite enough RAM for what you’re trying to do, then you’ll be at home here

Experience wrangling and analyzing data using Python or R
Experience with optimising AARRR funnels, A/B Testing and building dashboards that effectively communicate results and outcomes
A grounding in mathematics / statistics and a bachelor’s degree in a STEM area is preferred; but not required
Strong communication skills – verbal and written – be able to break down complex topics into simple solutions and ideas

Generous parental leave policy
Pet friendly offices including a garden, climbing wall, unisex toilets

Fun and quirky celebrations
Relocation budget provided for interstate or overseas candidates

We're growing our data science capabilities and are looking for a data scientist to join our Eliiza team in Melbourne.

NLP - sentiment analysis - social media, chatbot data, error correction

Information extraction - satellite image analysis, facial recognition, image processing
Who are we?
Glad you asked! We are Eliiza. Data science. Engineered for scale.
We are a passionate team of data scientists and engineers who apply data science and machine learning to solve real-world problems. Our mission is to create a bright future for Australian businesses and society in a world increasingly influenced by intelligent technologies.
We've created a culture that values diversity where people can truly be themselves! We care a lot about growing the Australian AI community in a positive direction, and we're doing several things to try and achieve that:

We produce the AI Australia podcast

We stream brown bag sessions to the broader community
We're also part of Mantel Group's 'house of brands' which means it's not just the Eliiza team you'll work with, learn from and see at social events - there's another 230 of us across DigIO, Kasna & CMD Solutions!
So you're ready for something new?
We're keen to know more about you! Our team is made up of a range of people, with different experience across a huge range of data driven skill sets.
If you're the right Data Scientist for us, you'll have:
an undergraduate degree in maths or statistics, or a postgraduate in broader disciplines such as the sciences
commercial data science experience across different industries and organisations
an understanding of key statistical and machine learning concepts across different areas of data science
the ability to manipulate complex data sets to visualise and model the data
experience using at least one open source data science language such as Python or R
fundamental software engineering skills
an awareness of relevant data and ML engineering concepts (e.g. database management, processing pipelines, and model deployment)
consulting experience, either with external clients or internally within an organisation
the ability to plan and implement the different phases of a data science project
a genuine passion for and connection to the data science and ML community
However, we value a diverse of skill-sets, and don't necessarily require that you're skilled with all of the above. If you feel you don't fit all the experience/skills listed above we still encourage you to apply or get in touch.
What's on offer if you join us?
We make sure you're always one step ahead by investing your learning and development, every year. We build our own training where it doesn't exist yet.
We hire smart people and get out of their way. By focusing on our five principles and not getting caught up in red tape, we trust you to get the job done.
You'll get all the tools you need - a new iPhone or Google phone, a new Macbook Pro or Dell, and a lot of branded swag!
But hold on, you mentioned a house of brands?
We certainly did! Mantel Group is an Australian-owned, 'house of brands' company with four technology businesses (Eliiza being one of them!) across Melbourne and Sydney. We're building a group of companies with open borders so we can support you to take on new skills without leaving an awesome team - we understand you won't have one job for life!
We may only be just over 2 years old but Mantel Group has already been recognised #9 in the 2020 Best Places to Work in Australia and #4 in the AFR's 2020 fastest growing new companies.
Keen to chat?

Click "Apply" to share your details with our talent team, and we'll be in touch.

In the meantime, check out 'how we hire' to find out what's in store if you're successful and get to know us better by visiting our website and following Eliiza on LinkedIn.

What's next?
Help us learn about you by submitting a complete and thoughtful application, which includes your resume. Your application and resume is a way for us to initially get to know you, so it's important to complete all relevant application questions so we have as much information about you as possible.
To start the application, you will be prompted to enter your email address. Your email address will be used to create and maintain your profile so make sure it is one you will have long term access to. Do not use an email address with ".edu" extension as doing so could result in delays receiving updates regarding your candidacy.
After you confirm your application, we will review it to determine whether you meet certain required qualifications.
If you are advanced to the next step of the process, you'll receive an email invitation to complete a series of 12 games through the pymetrics platform. Pymetrics will allow you to showcase your potential beyond what you tell us in your resume and application form. It's an additional data point that helps us gain a better understanding of who you are as an individual. It should take no longer than 25-35 minutes to complete. If you have already completed the pymetrics games, you will have the opportunity to submit your gameplay results for this specific application without having to replay the games.
Following completion of pymetrics, you'll receive another email invitation to complete a video interview, powered by HireVue. This is your opportunity to further bring your resume to life and showcase your experience for our recruiting team and hiring managers.
Both pymetrics and HireVue are required, and your application will not be considered for further review until you have completed them. We strongly encourage that you apply and complete these required elements as soon as possible, since programs will close as positions are filled.

Opportunity to join a team of passionate & supportive industry leading experts where you can really drive your future career
The purpose of Technical & Sustainability (T&S) in Anglo American is to drive the future of mining. To do this, we need wide-ranging information and organizational knowledge, both to support decision-making across our business, and to provide the raw material for accountability. Data Analytics teams process, analyse, share and visualize this information, aiding in the process of knowledge aggregation and transformation.
We are continually seeking new ways to bring our data together to inform big-picture decision-making, from pit to port, from sensor to desktop. Harnessing the power of data analytics enables us to link planning and operations and to unlock value across the full breadth of our operations.
Anglo American aspires to become the most valued mining company in the world. We're looking for talented people who share our values and our belief in a better future for mining. If you have the relevant skills and experience in Data Analytics, we'd like to hear from you.
Job Description
Programme Data Analyst
Reporting to the Principal Programme Manager – Data Analytics, you will be a key member of the Group Data Analytics Delivery team, and partner with relevant Business Unit SME’s to understand the questions they are trying to address to unlock value, and the data they have or need to collect to address the question and extract value. This role will be based in our Brisbane Corporate Office.
This role will be rewarding and varied and will see you:
Effectively and autonomously manage your own scope, priorities and deadlines across a number of data projects, with regular routine communication, and coordination with the Principal Programme Manager, project managers and business analysts.
Be the central point of contact for data discovery and data analysis for the relevant business unit data projects and provide expertise for other areas as required.
Refine opportunities and develop a pathway for value generating data projects and provide thought leadership on opportunities and technical direction
Perform exploratory data analysis and provide rapid iterations of analysis to refine posed problems, and identify potential solutions.
Assist and support Data Engineers in developing and deploying production workflows for taking data in real-time or periodically from sites / business functions, passing the data through the developed models and producing the relevant reporting without human intervention.
Work with and support the IM department and the business unit’s analytics centre on accessing relevant analytics tools and developed models.
Work with and support the IM department and the business unit’s analytics centre in the architecture of data analytics solutions as required.
Support regional Data Analytics Product Management with technical requirements analyses, advice and product backlog maintenance through stakeholder engagement and planning.

Qualifications
To be successful in this role, you will have the following:
Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, or Engineering.
Extensive experience in data analytics, preferably in the mining industry.
Experience in designing and managing complex data projects using the relevant Azure services or similar.
Demonstrated success working with multidisciplinary technical and global teams.
Extensive experience in Exploratory data analysis with the purpose of informing user requirements and solution design / architecture.
Extensive Experience in using SQL (and Python) and connecting to various structured and semi-structured data sources.
Experience with Agile Project Management Principles and using MS DevOps.
Working knowledge of common machine learning algorithms used in regression and classification is highly desirable.
Additional Information
What we offer
When you join Anglo American, you can expect to enjoy a competitive salary and benefits package. But more than this, you’ll find yourself in an environment where the opportunities for learning and growth are second to none. From technical training to leadership programmes, we bring out the best in our people. There are plenty of opportunities to move onwards and upwards too. We’re a large, successful multinational company – and we’re still growing all the time.
Who we are?
We aim to lead the industry by pursuing ever safer and more responsible ways of working, demonstrating integrity and showing care and respect for people and the planet. That means we are constantly seeking new opportunities to mine and process our products sustainably, using less water, less energy and more precise extraction technologies. As the custodians of coal and other precious natural resources – diamonds (through De Beers), copper, platinum and other precious metals, iron ore and nickel – our extraordinary teams work safely and collaboratively, with the utmost consideration for local communities, our customers and the world at large.
Inclusion and Diversity
We strive to create an inclusive environment for all employees. Women, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders are encouraged to apply for all vacant positions.
As well as a very competitive salary package, Anglo American offers exceptional training and development opportunities to all employees.
Apply today if you want to work with the latest technology and innovation, in an environment where we challenge you to drive positive change.

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest


Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1
Salary range: $74,406.00 - $100,090.00
Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

Key skills required
1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.
Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Weekend work required


Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

Victoria has developed a robust audit and risk methodology, now used across the country to understand the combustible cladding risk exposure to communities.
The purpose of CSV is to further enhance this methodology by supporting Victorian apartment owners to make their buildings safe and compliant. Initially a selection of buildings will be part of a pilot program of rectification which will inform expansion of the program to other buildings over time.

The purpose of Technical & Sustainability (T&S) in Anglo American is to drive the future of mining. To do this, we need wide-ranging information and organizational knowledge, both to support decision-making across our business, and to provide the raw material for accountability. Data Analytics teams process, analyse, share and visualize this information, aiding in the process of knowledge aggregation and transformation.
We are continually seeking new ways to bring our data together to inform big-picture decision-making, from pit to port, from sensor to desktop. Harnessing the power of data analytics enables us to link planning and operations and to unlock value across the full breadth of our operations.
Anglo American aspires to become the most valued mining company in the world. We're looking for talented people who share our values and our belief in a better future for mining. If you have the relevant skills and experience in Data Analytics, we'd like to hear from you.
Job Description
Programme Data Analyst
Reporting to the Principal Programme Manager – Data Analytics, you will be a key member of the Group Data Analytics Delivery team, and partner with relevant Business Unit SME’s to understand the questions they are trying to address to unlock value, and the data they have or need to collect to address the question and extract value. This role will be based in our Brisbane Corporate Office.
This role will be rewarding and varied and will see you:
Effectively and autonomously manage your own scope, priorities and deadlines across a number of data projects, with regular routine communication, and coordination with the Principal Programme Manager, project managers and business analysts.
Be the central point of contact for data discovery and data analysis for the relevant business unit data projects and provide expertise for other areas as required.
Refine opportunities and develop a pathway for value generating data projects and provide thought leadership on opportunities and technical direction
Perform exploratory data analysis and provide rapid iterations of analysis to refine posed problems, and identify potential solutions.
Assist and support Data Engineers in developing and deploying production workflows for taking data in real-time or periodically from sites / business functions, passing the data through the developed models and producing the relevant reporting without human intervention.
Work with and support the IM department and the business unit’s analytics centre on accessing relevant analytics tools and developed models.
Work with and support the IM department and the business unit’s analytics centre in the architecture of data analytics solutions as required.
Support regional Data Analytics Product Management with technical requirements analyses, advice and product backlog maintenance through stakeholder engagement and planning.

Qualifications
To be successful in this role, you will have the following:
Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, or Engineering.
Extensive experience in data analytics, preferably in the mining industry.
Experience in designing and managing complex data projects using the relevant Azure services or similar.
Demonstrated success working with multidisciplinary technical and global teams.
Extensive experience in Exploratory data analysis with the purpose of informing user requirements and solution design / architecture.
Extensive Experience in using SQL (and Python) and connecting to various structured and semi-structured data sources.
Experience with Agile Project Management Principles and using MS DevOps.
Working knowledge of common machine learning algorithms used in regression and classification is highly desirable.
Additional Information
What we offer
When you join Anglo American, you can expect to enjoy a competitive salary and benefits package. But more than this, you’ll find yourself in an environment where the opportunities for learning and growth are second to none. From technical training to leadership programmes, we bring out the best in our people. There are plenty of opportunities to move onwards and upwards too. We’re a large, successful multinational company – and we’re still growing all the time.
Who we are?
We aim to lead the industry by pursuing ever safer and more responsible ways of working, demonstrating integrity and showing care and respect for people and the planet. That means we are constantly seeking new opportunities to mine and process our products sustainably, using less water, less energy and more precise extraction technologies. As the custodians of coal and other precious natural resources – diamonds (through De Beers), copper, platinum and other precious metals, iron ore and nickel – our extraordinary teams work safely and collaboratively, with the utmost consideration for local communities, our customers and the world at large.
Inclusion and Diversity

Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1

Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.

Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Weekend work required
